<component type="desktop-application">
  <!--Created with jdAppStreamEdit 9.2-->
  <id>land.arcana.TarotCanvas</id>
  <name>Tarot Canvas</name>
  <summary>Desktop application for viewing and exploring tarot decks</summary>
  <developer id="ledif">
    <name>Adam Fidel</name>
  </developer>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license>
  <update_contact>adam@cloud.id</update_contact>
  <description>
    <p>Tarot Canvas is a cross-platform application for viewing and exploring tarot decks. It supports decks that are compliant with the Tarot Deck Specification v1.0.</p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Explore tarot deck imagery, metadata and esoterica (corrospondences and other occult or divinatory information)</li>
      <li>Includes the traditional Rider-Waite-Smith deck and supports any deck following Arcana Land's tarot deck specification</li>
      <li>Provides a playground canvas where you can place and arrange tarot cards from any deck</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
